data.description:
This historic home in Saugatuck offers a unique blend of stately charm, spaciousness, and picturesque surroundings. Situated on almost 2 acres overlooking Clearbrook Golf Course and adjacent to Goshorn Creek, the setting is serene and captivating. The popular Clearview Grill Room nearby adds convenience and dining opportunities.
The main house, boasting nearly 3,000 square feet of living space, seamlessly combines elegance with comfort. With 3 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms, there's ample room for residents and guests alike. Meticulously updated and maintained, the property exudes timeless appeal.
The spacious kitchen, equipped with commercial-grade appliances, is a chef's delight. A lovely formal dining room provides an ideal setting for gatherings. The large living room, with natural fireplace, offers stunning views of the golf course greens and fairways.
Adding to the property's allure is a separate guest house, offering versatility and potential for additional living space or rental income. Priced competitively, this property presents a rare opportunity to own a piece of Saugatuck's history while enjoying modern amenities and a prime location. Don't miss the chance to make this charming estate your own. Owners have contracted to have a new roof installed.
